President Juan Manuel Santos of Colombia will be visiting the White House on February 4, 2016 for an official working visit. The purpose of the visit is to hold a bilateral meeting and commemorate 15 years of bipartisan cooperation through Plan Colombia, a joint effort to create a safer and more prosperous future for Colombians. The visit will also provide an opportunity to celebrate the successful partnership between the United States and Colombia, support President Santos' efforts to achieve a peace accord with the FARC, and discuss future collaboration in the event of a historic peace agreement.